			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Farslayer77 wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Anyone have any experience with reflect ?</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
I think it would be quite useful in PvP. In other situations, it is of limited use (or rather, in 99% of all cases I can make better use of my spell slots). The duration is quite short (2 tics), so you will have to react quite fast if you want to use it effectively.
<br />

<br />
The description says it gives you a chance to reflect a spell, however it seems to always reflect nukes partially (so you still take some damage), while single effects like root are fully reflected. One interesting thing I noticed is that DoTs seem to be fully reflected also (fun to see a high level DoT being bounced back <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="Smile" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
Overall, dont make this spell a priority (except perhaps if you PvP a lot).<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=423546" target="_blank" class="postlink">Izudin</a>, 65 Arch Convoker on Quellious</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
