			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Burning sands is asstastic, the mana cost for damage blows and the short cast time is not a big enough advantage to mem it for anything other than farming greens in dungeons. Learn to time nukes better.
<br />

<br />
Protection of Callaiv is the best mage spell in a long long long time for raiders. Making your pet immune to AEs has been a holy grail for a long time. Also a nice help if your attention slips and you're slow in pulling pet off an enraging mob. For a raider PoC > DPoC IMHO (although obviously any pet focus is uber).
<br />

<br />
I find Reflect/Bounce is hard to time. Trash mobs never land spells on me ... as in ever ... so I only use it for duels in the arena. Basically a novelty spell on a PvE server.
<br />

<br />
Wind of the Desert isn't too bad at all. Casting time should be reduced by 1 to 1.5 seconds but the recast is OK and the damage is very nice. Good compliment to Scintillation.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=86257" target="_blank" class="postlink">Zaniel Stormseeker</a>
<br />
Arch Convoker of <a href="http://www.afflictionguild.com" target="_blank" class="postlink">Affliction</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
